Our Brisbane office is growing and we would love to meet passionate C++
engineers.

Blackmagic Design creates the world’s highest quality video editing products,
digital film cameras, colour correctors, video converters, video monitoring,
routers, live production switchers, disk recorders, waveform monitors and real
time film scanners for the feature film, post production and television
broadcast industries.

More importantly, Blackmagic Design’s products are accessible for everybody
from Oscar-winning production companies and cinematographers to educational
institutions and 15-year-old high school students.

Team facts

  * Established large team of Engineers working on C++ in the Mac/Windows/Linux GUI application space. 
  * Collaborative development inter/intra team 
  * Work closely with strong Software Engineering , Embedded Engineering and Product Design teams 
  * Get hands on with building end to end- prototype to final hardware 

Desirable Tech Skills

  * Fluent programming skills and implementing solutions using C++ 
  * Knowledge of Qt and modern C++ (C++11, 14 and 17) 
  * Linux, Mac OS X or UNIX development experience 
  * History of building custom made products 
  * Experience with multi process or threaded applications 
  * Experience with complex data structures 
  * Scripting experience (python preferred) 
  * Ability to handwrite code with a willingness to discuss 

We are a creative, flexible team with a small company mentality very much
still in play.

Get in touch if you would like to join our growing Brisbane office.

  

